The incident involves mutual physical altercation between parties with comparable fault (both received administrative penalties). Plaintiff’s dominant pathology—acute decompensation of long-standing coronary disease, ischemic cardiomyopathy and heart failure—predated the confrontation; the trauma merely acted as a trigger. Consequently, only the objectively verifiable, directly attributable out-of-pocket expenses survive causation and apportionment scrutiny:

- a fraction of the documented medical receipts proportionate to the minor traumatic component (head/chest contusion) rather than cardiac treatment;  
- three days of level-2 nursing at the regulated rate;  
- modest transportation and inpatient meal allowances tied exclusively to the 29–31 August admission.  

Lost-earnings and subsequent multi-week sick-leave certificates are rejected because they arise from the pre-existing cardiac condition, not from any injury inflicted by defendant. After netting the parties’ respective degrees of fault, the net award that satisfies both tort principles and the evidentiary record is 1351 yuan.

