The court, applying PRC Tort Liability Law and Supreme People’s Court personal-injury guidelines to the proved facts, awards only those heads of loss that are both causally linked to the minor injuries (轻微伤) and supported by evidence:

- medical expenses are reduced to the portion directly attributable to the contusions and acute head injury (pre-existing cataract, sensorineural deafness and anxiety are excluded), yielding a net medical award of RMB 5 200;
- hospital meal subsidy is allowed at the statutory per-diem rate for 15 in-patient days (RMB 900);
- nursing care is allowed at the local standard for 15 days (RMB 1 050);
- transport costs are allowed on receipts (RMB 238);
- nutrition and mental-distress claims are disallowed—nutrition is not separately proved and mental-damage solatium is not awarded for simple minor injuries that resulted only in administrative detention.

The arithmetic total is therefore RMB 7 388. All other heads claimed (full medical expenses, nutrition fee, mental solatium, apology order) are rejected.

