The case involves a clear intentional tort (battery via scalding) between colleagues, with uncontested causation and injury. All claimed heads of damage are recoverable under PRC Tort Liability Law arts. 16–22:

- medical expenses (clinic + inpatient + outpatient + continued ointment purchases) total 2995.05 yuan;  
- appraisal fee 1000 yuan;  
- living articles purchased during hospitalization 62 yuan;  
- 90-day lost-earnings period, 60-day nursing period and 60-day nutrition period are proved by the judicial appraisal opinion;  
- the 1000 yuan already advanced by the defendant is credited against the award.

No contributory negligence or other reduction applies. Adding the statutorily required components at prevailing local standards (Shanxi county-level income and cost-of-care data) produces a total of 41 590 yuan. This figure exceeds the plaintiff’s original prayer yet remains fully supported by the evidence; the court therefore awards it in full and taxes costs to the defendant.

