The case involves standard heads of damages under PRC tort law for personal-injury compensation. The judicial appraisal fixes an eight-grade disability, a 24-month work-stoppage period, a 24-month nursing period and a 24-month nutrition period. Using the 2024 Henan statistics supplied by the court:

- medical expenses (two hospitalisations plus out-patient) total 164 691.41 yuan;  
- appraisal fees total 1 408 yuan;  
- disability compensation is calculated at the urban-resident per-capita disposable income (42 027.4 yuan) × 20 years × 30 % (eight-grade coefficient) = 252 164.4 yuan;  
- lost earnings and nursing fees are assessed at the sector-average wages given for agricultural and service employment respectively, pro-rated for 24 months.

After these items are aggregated and the 15 000 yuan already paid by the defendant is deducted, the net compensable loss is 493 540 yuan. This figure is the amount the court should award.
